headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox scored 30 points, Tyrese Haliburton had a career-high 28 and the Sacramento Kings completed their longest road trip of the season with a 119-105 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox scores 30, Haliburton has 28 as Kings beat Cavs 119-105

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 31 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder relied on strong 3-point shooting Monday night to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 112-103.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder use 3-point barrage to beat Timberwolves 112-103

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Gordon Hayward scored 27 points, Terry Rozier added 24 and the Charlotte Hornets held on to beat the San Antonio Spurs 100-97 on Monday night in their first game since losing LaMelo Ball to injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets top Spurs 100-97 in first game since Ball's injury

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 30 points, Rudy Gobert added 21 points, 10 rebounds and a career-high nine blocks, and the Utah Jazz pounded the Chicago Bulls 120-95 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell, Gobert dominate as Jazz beat Bulls 120-95

headlines.description: — The Houston Rockets ended their 20-game losing streak Monday night, as John Wall had his first triple-double in five years in a 117-99 victory over the Toronto Raptors.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets end skid at 20, Wall has 1st triple-double since '16

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 29 points and nine assists, and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Boston Celtics 132-126 in overtime on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant, Brooks lead Grizzlies past Celtics in overtime

headlines.description: — Jrue Holiday had 28 points and 14 assists, and the Milwaukee Bucks overcame the absence of Giannis Antetokoumpo to breeze past the Indiana Pacers 140-113 on Monday night for their seventh consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks trounce Pacers 140-113 without injured Antetokounmpo

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 25 points, Terance Mann added a season-high 21 and the Los Angeles Clippers rallied from a 22-point deficit in the second half to snap the Atlanta Hawks' eight-game winning streak with a 119-110 victory Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reserves lead Clippers' huge rally to 119-110 win over Hawks
